# Entity

This rule describe meta information of generic data type generation pattern.

---
## Identity
Field Identity triggering definition of Identity of <EntityName>

**Example:**
```
ID: Identity of Tenant
```
Generates:
```go
import "github.com/google/uuid"
type TenantID uuid.UUID
```

---
### Enumerated String 
Field Enumerated string triggering definition of EnumeratedString of <EntityName>+<FieldName> 

**Example:**
```
Status: Enumerated String of "active", "inactive", default "active"
```
Generates:
```go
type TenantStatus string

const (
    TenantStatusActive   TenantStatus = "active"
    TenantStatusInactive TenantStatus = "inactive"
    TenantStatusDefault  TenantStatus = TenantStatusActive // Default value
)
```

---
### Constructor
Entity Definition also generates constructor with field with **constructor input** tags as args

**Example:**
```
ID: Identity of Tenant // constructor input
Name: string // constructor input
Status: Tenant Status // constructor input
CreatedAt: time.Time
```
Generates:
```go
func NewTenant(id TenantID, name string, status TenantStatus) *Tenant {
    return &Tenant{
        ID:     id,
        Name:   name,
        Status: status,
        // other fields set to zero value or handled separately
    }
}
``` 